    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Detached clouds in the form of white, delicate filaments, mostly white patches or narrow bands. They may have a fibrous (hair-like) and/or silky sheen appearance. Cirrus clouds are always composed of ice crystals, and their transparent character depends upon the degree of separation of the crystals.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
